## Your Complete Toolkit

All tools are in `tools/`. Run via `python tools/<name>.py <args>`.

### Robinhood MCP Tools (via execute_trade.py or direct MCP calls)

**Portfolio & Positions**
- `get_all_positions` — **USE THIS FIRST** when asked about positions. Returns ALL open stock AND option positions in one call with P&L.
- `get_positions` — Open stock positions (ticker, qty, avg cost, current price)
- `get_option_positions` — Open option positions with full Greeks (delta, gamma, theta, vega, IV), P&L per contract, mark price, volume, OI
- `get_account` / `get_account_snapshot` — Portfolio value, buying power, cash
- `get_order_history` — Recent stock and option orders with status and fill data

**Market Data**
- `get_quote` — Real-time stock quote (bid, ask, volume, previous close)
- `get_nbbo` — National Best Bid/Offer with spread in bps (cached 500ms)
- `get_option_chain` — Full chain at an expiry (strike, bid, ask, volume, OI)
- `get_option_greeks` — Real-time Greeks for a specific contract (delta, gamma, theta, vega, rho, IV, chance of profit)

**Order Execution**
- `place_stock_order` — Stock limit order with fill polling
- `place_option_order` — Options limit order with fill polling
- `smart_limit_order` — NBBO-pegged limit order (preferred for stocks)
- `place_order_with_stop_loss` — Main order + companion stop-loss
- `place_order_with_buffer` — Limit order with % price buffer
- `close_position` — Market-sell stock shares
- `close_option_position` — Close option contracts (sell-to-close)
- `cancel_and_close` — Cancel stop + market-sell
- `modify_stop_loss` — Adjust stop-loss price (trailing)
- `get_order_status` — Check fill/status of an order

**Watchlist**
- `add_to_watchlist` / `remove_from_watchlist` / `get_watchlist`

